We’re nearing the end of the calendar year and about to “go out” with a bang of a Full Moon Gemini this week. The theme this week is A W A R E N E S S because with all the heated energy from the Full Moon PLUS the opportunities for positive shifting, I want you to be aware of what’s “moving” you.  
 
The Full Moon isn’t all that’s in the stars … 
 
The Moon is conjunct Mars retrograde making things a bit heated and tense.  If you can remember that tension creates change than it will be “fine”.  If you can remember to channel this Mars energy effectively, then no-one will get hurt.  (haha) And, if you can remember that all the things “coming up for review” come up for clearing so you can shift your life … 
 
This is “life”  … always flowing .. always moving.  
 
Saturn has a say in the energy this week.  A bit serious, persistent, and patient – that IS Saturn. Take responsibility for your actions and move with an inner confidence that moves mountains with just a look.
 
Venus square Jupiter will bring opportunities of joy, optimism, and harmony so that’s always nice!  Neptune direct gives you the go ahead to follow your dreams and use your intuition as your guidepost!

Why do you run away from awareness?  The answer is easy:  It’s actually easier to stay asleep to your life, than it is to do the “work”. It’s easier to point the finger at others, blame others, and fall victim to a life you cannot control.  It’s easier to think that there is an “other”, when in reality, everything is just a reflection of your thoughts. 
 
Once you become awake and aware, you may not always enjoy the ride, but you know that it’s all for your highest and best good.  You understand that you are responsible for every choice in your life, and when you stop, if only for a moment, before making a choice, and become AWARE of the feeling, or the motivation behind that choice … well you may choose differently.  
 
Now let that sink in and just guess how many of those 90,000 thoughts were acted upon, without awareness.  Welcome to being a spiritual being living in an Earth suit. Welcome to Earth School.  

📸 @allliiibaba

This is the Final Full Moon of the YEAR and although it is, overall positive and affirming, there are some powerful aspects that make it a bit angsty, if you will.  Let’s just say AWARENESS is key in this energy.  
 
Full Moon Gemini ~ 12.7.2022 at 8:08pm pst is ruled by Mercury governing movement, communication, information and is asking you to please be aware of your thoughts, words, and actions.  The Moon is EXACTLY conjunct Mars retrograde /opposite the Sun; what does this mean?  That internal gaze you’ve been refining, will be triggered by exactly what you’ve been calling in.  
 
We ask to cultivate patience; we get experiences that give us the opportunity to refine patience.  That’s the energy right now.  So be AWARE of what you’ve been asking for and know that it’s all about QUANTUM HEALING.  
 
Remember that Gemini sees two sides to everything so be curious. Don’t run from the uncomfortable – get in there and see the gift it has to offer.  Saturn trine the Sun, sextile the Moon:  well, Saturn by nature is the keeper of time and karma.  So, take responsibility for your life, your choices, and everything that has happened “to” you. Understand that YOU are the ONLY one that can authentically shift your frequency.  It’s an invitation to wake up to your power, and how you function in this Earth suit.  
 
Neptune is now direct so use your intuition; Saturn will keep you honest, and Mars retrograde will support you in using your energy effectively. Listen deeply right now … and maybe for always.

Merry Happy Everything

{WINTER GIFTS, DIYS AND HOLIDAY FUN} - DAY SIX⁠
⁠
If you are anything like me, you are all about spreading cheer with a little DIY! 🍬 This candy cane scrub only requires a few ingredients and will make great gifts or a perfect item to have on hand for a little self-care treat!⁠
⁠
What you need: ⁠
⁠
✔️ ¾ cup white cane sugar⁠
✔️ ½ cup Fractionated Coconut Oil⁠
✔️ 12 drops Peppermint Oil ⁠
✔️ Skin safe food coloring⁠
⁠
Combine sugar and fractionated coconut oil in a bowl and divide the mixture equally into 2 bowls. In one of the bowls add the skin-safe food coloring. Layer red and white to create the candy cane effect. ⁠
⁠
👉 What other essential oils would you use to make this scrub up?⁠

As I reflect on the year it’s astounding to me how much time I spent healing. At the tail end of 2021, I got the vid. It attacked all bits of inflammation in my body making it hard to move my head and neck.  The burning in my neck was intolerable, and chiropractic adjustments became impossible.  All backbends, chaturangas, jumping jacks, and burpees were out of the question.  Pilates, bootcamp, spin class, a full yoga session, and even running was out of the question.  I couldn’t even sit at my alter in the morning and journal, it hurt too much.  
 
I had no choice but to surrender to the pain and rest.  My weeks were consumed with physical therapy, acupuncture, and alternating heat and cold on my neck and spine.  I walked around with my Tens machine on for hours in the morning and put Moxa on trigger points at night.  Sauna and cold plunge was key.  Lying in bed in the morning on my posture pump became my meditation.  
 
This was my 2022.  Healing.  
 
Remember your body is a vessel, and it harbors all the pain that has been unexpressed and the energy of your ancestors.  Pain is most often, something emotional coming to the surface.  I can say that after all this time and energy, approximately 100 physical therapy appointments, 48 acupuncture sessions, countless breathwork and restorative yoga sessions, I feel about 95% better.  So, I finally participated in a journey.  I took the medicine and went to the Source.  To sit with the issues underneath that hold the seed to that pain.  
 
It was beautiful, painful, and awakening.  Here’s the deal: 
 
✨You don’t owe anyone anything, work on your Self.
✨Drop into your heart without apology.
✨Forgive yourself.
✨Ask what would love do.
✨Balance joy and healing
✨You are already whole and complete, you never need to be fixed.
 
I feel even more aware than ever before, and so grateful the pain has left my body.  Now onto expansion of the heart.

{WINTER GIFTS, DIYS AND HOLIDAY FUN} - DAY TWELVE⁠
⁠
🍫Snacking chocolates infused with dōTERRA essential oils make a quick and easy item to bring to any event, give as a gift or even keep for yourself!⁠
⁠
What you need: 1 cup dark chocolate chips, 1 tsp coconut oil, ½ cup almonds, Peppermint and/or Wild Orange essential oil.⁠
⁠
Place chocolate chips and coconut oil in a double boiler or you can put a glass bowl on top of a gentle boiling pot of water and melt until smooth. Add in essential oil of choice (note: 1-2 drops is perfect for a subtle taste, add more as needed!) ⁠
⁠
Pour melted chocolate onto wax paper on a cookie sheet and spread the chocolate around with a spoon. Crush almonds (or candy canes!) and sprinkle over the chocolate layer. Place in the refrigerator and allow to chill. Once solidified, break into pieces and enjoy!⁠
⁠
Which are you making: Peppermint with candy cane or Wild Orange with almonds?⁠

This week’s theme is 

C R E A T I V I T Y.  

The week starts off with a triple (3) code (12.12.12) and that in and of itself oozes creativity.  Remember that life is NOT about deadlines, strategies, obligations, and responsibilities. Yes, that is part of being human but mostly … the creative energy is what our soul yearns for.  
 
We are just coming off a Jupiter / Venus square that ignited an elevation of awareness.  A heightened consciousness if you will.  Use your intuition and take a risk!  Stop scrolling to see what other people are doing and just do you!  Be a creative genius, aligned with Source! 
 
The Sun sextile Saturn will make you more observant – watch intently.  The Sun will also square Neptune: expand your intuition, write down those dreams, and listen to your inner voice.  These to aspects to the Sun will make it easier to take that leap of faith, to lead with your heart, to have the courage to do the “thing”. Remember that abundance is simply a currency of energy; allow yourself to FEEL that flow.  *hint – this flow happens in the being, not in the doing. 
 
Mercury trine Uranus will support all levels of thinking.  From higher mind, inspiring creativity to day-to-day reality, observe and listen for those moments when imagination is trying to creep in.  Don’t block it with linear thinking, allow it to flow.  Stop hustling with the crowd and listen to your inner genius.

{WINTER GIFTS, DIYS AND HOLIDAY FUN} - DAY TWENTY⁠-ONE⁠
⁠
Another day, another DIY! 😆 Today we are going to talk about making our own essential oil candles!⁠
⁠
What you will need: 4 cups beeswax pellets, 1 cup of coconut oil, cotton wicks, 4 oz mason jars, and your favorite essential oils.⁠
⁠
Melt the beeswax and coconut oil in the microwave. While still a liquid, add your essential oils (I suggest 20 drops Holiday Joy, 20 drops Holiday Peace or 20 drops Northern Escape). Add a drop of wax to the center of the mason jar and position the wick. Carefully pour the wax mixture into the mason jars and allow the candles to set and cool. Cut the wick to about ½ inch about the wax. This will make 4 candles.⁠
⁠
How many of these are you going to make? This is a great way to ditch those toxic candles once and for all!⁠

On this gorgeous Winter Solstice Day, the Sun moves into Capricorn … the sign of the goat. What a glorious energy to be moving into at the end of the year, as it really shines a light on what to expect in 2023.  
 
In just a couple of days, the Capricorn New Moon takes place at one degree of the zodiac sign, a very karmic point of new beginnings.  Not only that, but the next several New Moons happen at one degree … talk about auspicious. 
 
There’s a lot to unpack with this New Moon so I invite you to listen to the full forecast on my Youtube channel and be prepared to take notes.  In a nutshell, this New Moon is about stepping into your power; it’s about rising above the density of this Earth DESPITE your fears, doubts, and perceived flaws.  
 
Are you ready for that new start?  Four planets are here to support you:  Venus, Mercury, Pluto, and the Moon join the Sun in Capricorn:  supporting you in manifesting your desires and actually building something that stands the test of time.  
 
On 12.20.22 Jupiter moved into Aries which is ALL about moving beyond your fears and doubts.  12.21.22 is the Solstice and Capricorn Season.  And on 12.23.22 not only do we have a SUPER New Moon in Capricorn, SQUARING Jupiter, but Chiron (sacred healer) also goes direct after retrograding since July 2022. 
 
Time to let the past go. Take responsibility for what’s yours and then be done already.  Envision your dream and if you’ve been taking steps to get there .. keep going.

I did breathwork this morning for the first time after my medicine journey two weeks ago.  I could feel the collective energy getting to me, burying the profound insights I had that day.  I had been cracked open wider than ever before, and “life” was starting to get to me. 
 
Breathwork is profound – magic – powerful; it travels to your cells, meeting your soul in some other realm.  When I practice breath, I watch myself yawn, distracting myself from the task at hand … today that happened only once.  My soul wanted to go deep – and that it did.  Tears were the product of my session today – but not sad tears. Tears of realization – intense clarity of my path, both forward and backward.  For the first time, the tears were not of grief or buried rage, they were an offering.  
 
I dedicated my breath to my mother, my father, my children, and all those suffering.  I remembered that I am an infinite being, and I was shown the next path.  What a gift.  
 
I’ll be offering breathwork a lot come January – both in person and online.  I hope you will try it.  Some sessions will be recorded so you can practice at home but my invitation to you is to allow yourself to be held in this practice.  Be brave and clear the stagnation so you can truly see what’s real.  More soon.

Mercury goes into retrograde today, joining Mars in the quest to slow down.  These are two very powerful planets in retrograde today.  Then why would I host an intention setting breathwork/sound healing session?  
 
Here’s a few reasons: 
 
·      Breathwork removes stagnation in the body, offering up space for you to feel into what’s real
·      Sound healing calms the nervous system – returning you to your center 
·      From that place we ask
o   What did I overcome this last year
o   What did I accomplish
o   How do I feel about the present situation of my life
o   What do I really desire
 
I do not advise you to act and begin taking steps towards whatever it is you think you desire. Instead, I invite you to feel into your subtle body, write down the information that comes up for you, and then sit with it.  For a bit … 
 
You see, the Capricorn New Moon aligned with Jupiter, and Chiron went direct. Meaning your lessons are all coming forward.  They are sitting at the forefront of your heart and mind.  The key to Chiron is to notice them, embrace them, and use them.  But it’s all still unfolding. If you hurry to the next thing (2023) you’ll miss this most powerful gift.  
 
My advice?  Clean house, clear your thoughts, purge your heart.  Gain clarity but exercise patience.
 
The Full Moon Cancer will bring emotions to the surface, allowing you to purge more.  (1.6.23) and then finally, the New Moon Aquarius (1.21.22) which is the day before Chinese New Year 2023.  And that my friends, is when the time to really drop in will land … The intentions you set, and start out working on 12.31.22, will most likely have more kinks to work through.  Of course you do you, but know that the Moon makes the waves.

The first Full Moon of 2023 falls in the sensitive sign of Cancer this Friday, 1.6.2023.  Cancer is the hard-shelled-soft-on-the-inside Crab and that is completely the vibe of this Full Moon.  
 
Still burrowing in Mercury and Mars retrograde, we are celebrating the New calendar year with stillness, purging, and organizing.
 
We have so many amazing transits coming up in the next month, but for now, the best thing we can do is rest in the energy of this Full Moon.  
The Full Moon is sextile/trine to Uranus which suggest swift changes, liberating outcomes, and rapid movement already this 2023.   The most powerful thing you can do in this type of energy is listen to your intuition.  The proverbial “veil” has again, been lifted and we are afforded an opportunity to grow, expand, and overcome our obstacles.  Listen deeply before reacting … Mars is a little instigator.  No need to blow up for no reason.  
 
The Moon/Sun is also square to Chiron, the healer of all healers.  This is potent healing energy … don’t waste it.  
 
Cancer IS the Moon; it IS the Mother… allow yourself to be nourished during this time.  Your inner strength is being renewed and revitalized so use this time for reflection and purging out the old.  
 
Mercury and Mars are both direct by 1.18.2023 and the first New Moon of the year is 1.21.2023.  I say be still  - allow yourself to be held, nurtured, and loved … let your sensitive Crab be loved.

Console (Comforting Blend) is a blend of trees and flowers formulated to assist those in need of emotional comfort. This week’s theme is C O U R A G E … Having that heart-centered courage to reform the way you live and experience this life.  Tall order, I know but everything is shifting.  
 
First off, the numerology for this year is (7) seven (2+0+2+3=7):  change, philosophy, higher-mind thinking, inspiration.  
 
The upcoming Full Moon Leo is the (5th) fifth Full Moon in a row at 16 degrees (that’s 7 by the way).  
 
Uranus square the Sun and the Moon, creating a T-square ON the Full Moon:  change and unexpected shifts, offering you freedom.  But what do we do when we are offered change?  We cling to what was comfortable, and we try and keep things the same.  Change is inevitable and you must have the COURAGE to trust that God knows best. That Divine timing is everything. And that accepting impermanence is one of the keys to life.  
 
My invitation for you this week is to get clear about what is working and what isn’t.  Get clear on where you are, and where you want to be.  And then set those boundaries, be disciplined, and be open to a new way of being.  Ask for wisdom and guidance; and when you do, get quiet enough to hear the answer.

When we step into this role as a “leader” but know we are always a student, the confident humility shines through. I have a little issue with our society “sensationalizing” ancient, mystic practices.  It’s a real sore spot for me because I know that’s where all your attention is going.  I would investigate that perhaps. ⁠
⁠
My personal journey started out on the yoga mat.  Unraveling the density of my lineage through movement.  One day I felt the energy in my body and started crying … that’s when I became a Reiki III teacher.  In a class one afternoon, a woman called me a “Priestess” to which I laughed, but shivers went up and down my spine when she said it.  From there, I went down the path of Archetypes, Priestess, and Shaman training.  For years I dabbled with sound, vibration and breathwork and now, they are part of my healing bag of tricks.  And of course, essential oils have been there all along. All the while raising two young women on my own.⁠
⁠
Point is, we are always learning, ever evolving.  The breath has unlocked deep wounds and let in the light for healing in my own life.  It’s like unraveling 20 years of therapy in one 40-minute session. ⁠
⁠
I’m not going to post photos of my students/clients having a visceral experience … in my humble opinion, that’s an overshare.  I am however, going to ask you to try it.  I think you’d be surprised at the intensity of your ability to stay focused and truly release all that is holding you back. ⁠

Unfortunately, commercial dish detergent is loaded with awful chemicals that coat everything you eat off of. So here is an alternative that you can make right at home and have comfort knowing you aren’t washing your dishes in harmful chemicals!⁠
⁠
1 cup baking soda⁠
¼ cup citric acid⁠
1 tbsp On Guard Cleaner Concentrate⁠
5 drops Grapefruit essential oil (or any citrus)⁠
⁠
✅ Directions:⁠
⁠

2. Place in silicone molds and let sit for 4 hours.⁠
3. Remove tabs and store them in an airtight container. Use in place of store-bought tablets!⁠
⁠

The intention of SOUL MEDICINE is to offer you, the listener, ways to reconnect to your soul.   This week I talk about Breathwork (again) and how it has awakened me. Not just to myself, my patterns, my trauma, or my gifts ... but also how it has awakened me to life. It’s a crazy world we live in ... one that is not slowing down anytime soon. If you’re not paying attention you are most likely getting sucked up into the void of algorithms, distracting content, unnecessary overthinking, other peoples judgments, and the 1D world. 

The funny thing is none of this will matter at the end of your life. The things you feel anxious over now, most likely will not mean a damn thing at the end of your life. How you lived will matter. Who you spent time with, will matter. How you loved will matter. How you served will matter. 

All the other stuff .. not important. 

And yet, I sit in an airport watching people NOT make eye contact hunch over their phones, and completely distract themselves. It’s not for me ... and yet, I too can fall into that .. So I practice breathwork. Yoga used to do it for me .. but that is just a layer ... breathwork goes deeper. And if you are to live a life that is truly your own, you must get past that subterranean hum of anxiety that overlays it all ... trust me. 

Listen to this episode and gain a deeper understanding around the practice of breathwork, how I found it, why I think it’s important and how to avoid falling into “line” with life.

Did you know that you can make your own All-Purpose wipes? If you are a recovering Big Brand wipe addict like myself, then this is the best news ever!⁠
⁠
✅ All you need is:⁠
1 roll premium paper towels⁠
2 cups warm water⁠
2 tbsp Fractionated Coconut Oil (FCO)⁠
5 drops On Guard⁠
1-2 tbsp OnGuard Foaming Hand Wash⁠
⁠
✅ How to DIY them:⁠
⁠
1. Cut the paper towel roll in half widthwise with a serrated knife. Use one half now and save the other for later!⁠
2. Combine water, FCO, essential oils, and Hand Wash in a small bowl⁠
3. Pour mixture over paper towels and cover with an airtight lid. Let absorb for 10 minutes.⁠
4. Flip the container over and let it sit another 10 minutes.⁠
5. Remove and discard the cardboard tube. Pull the wipes from the center when you are ready to use them!⁠
⁠
Do this once and see just how simple it is to make these non-toxic wipes that even your kids can use to help you clean! ⁠
⁠

My brand is Dana Damara Evolution because it’s my personal belief that we all evolve throughout our life.  For some it’s subtle, shifting 2 degrees at a time – a little here and a little there. For others – life hits them hard, and they are forced to evolve.  And for others … it’s just part of who they are.  I’ve made a life out of grounding into the values I hold around healing.  Shifting layers of myself, consistently letting go, learning new skills, embodying wisdom, and moving into the unknown.  
 
I watch many people begin “healing journeys” and then get stuck.  Stuck in believing that they aren’t healed and have “all this work to do.” And while I do believe that we are here to “work”, it’s more about coming back home to who you are.  It’s about accepting the beauty and perfection of where you’ve been, where you are, and where you are headed, even if it’s unknown.  
 
And if you can accept that this life is a spiral and not about “getting anywhere” then the concept of evolving as a spiritual being in this human Earth suit makes sense.  Every conflict, every pattern, every challenge becomes a part of you.  You aren’t “leaving anything behind”. You aren’t “becoming someone new”. You are evolving into versions of yourself … hopefully at a higher frequency of understanding this life and how you roll in it.  
 
These photos are of me and a snippet of my journey.  From yoga studio owner in the NW to sound healer in So Cal.  All the labels, the titles, the hustling, the allowing … over two decades.  It’s crazy to witness.  And it’s just a snippet.  All of this and it’s just a particle of “who I am” … just a little particle.  
 
Can you take a moment and look at your life … what you’ve done, how far you’ve come, and how much you’ve evolved?  It’s so satisfying and quite incredible.

This DIY recipe for makeup remover wipes will cleanse and nourish the skin all while removing your makeup for the day. ⁠
⁠
Ingredients:⁠
2 tablespoons witch hazel⁠
2 tablespoons Fractionated Coconut Oil⁠
2 tablespoons distilled water⁠
1–2 drops Tea Tree oil⁠
Roll of paper towels⁠
⁠
✅ Directions: ⁠
⁠
1. Combine witch hazel, Fractionated Coconut Oil, and water in a small bowl and stir.⁠
2. Add Tea Tree essential oil.⁠
3. Use a serrated knife to cut the roll of paper towels in half widthwise and remove the tube from one half.⁠
4. Put the half without the tube in an airtight container, then pour the solution over the roll.⁠
5. Replace lid and shake.⁠
6. To use, pull wipes from the center and wipe off makeup.⁠
⁠

One of my favorite things to do is to share this practice with those people who want to dive deep.  

I am a teacher of teachers. 

I like to watch students come to a yoga training (online or in person) and be so intrigued with life, that they shift their energy in ways they couldn’t have imagined.  
 
I hosted my first 200-hour training in 2006, some 18 years ago, in Washington State. This training has grown to include other teachers, peers, students who opened their own yoga studio, became birthing doulas with yoga training, sound healers, and energy medicine practitioners.  We’ve had physical therapists, chiropractors, body workers, and stay at home parents.
 
You need no background to learn this practice of yoga. In fact, it’s better to come in as open as possible.  

But be aware, once you step foot on this path, you can never go back to sleep. And you will yearn for learning for the rest of your life. You will open portals to your heart that you didn’t know existed, breakthrough barriers of not-enoughness, and create pathways of healing through your own learning and sharing. 
 
Yes, you CAN make a living “teaching yoga”… do not get swallowed up by the stories that tell you otherwise – it’s an illusion.  All you need to do is take one step.  The common excuses I hear: 
 
🔹 I will wait until I can do the whole thing in person.
🔹 I don’t have enough yoga experience.
🔹 My kids are too little.
🔹 I don’t have the money. 
🔹 I don’t like learning online.
🔹 I don’t have what it takes … I need accountability.
 
All excuses from the ego to not step on the path to awakening.  To continue an existence of sleep walking, as Michael Beckwith calls it. To continue to blame external circumstances for your life as Byron Katie says.  And to opt out of living your best life.  
 
My creedo:  

✨Truth – freedom – love.  ✨

Not always easy and graceful, but necessary to awaken to the power of you.

The intention of SOUL MEDICINE is to offer you, the listener, ways to reconnect to your soul.  This week I’m talking Yamas and Niyamas. Now obviously I am just skimming the surface with this podcast.  The philosophy that holds the foundation of the yoga practice is everything.  We cannot hold a “steady comfortable pose” if we are scattered in the mind. If are spewing resentment instead of gratitude. If are not upholding the truth that lives in our own hearts.  

The (8) Limbs of Yoga are powerful benchmarks that hold me to my truth every single day. The Yamas and the Niyamas spell out the 10 “code of ethics” are valuable for an awakened existence.  Yamas are the attitudes towards others and the world around you. 
✨Ahimsa or non-violence: Compassion for all living things 
✨Satya or truthfulness: Commitment to the truth 
✨Asteya or non-stealing: Not taking anything that has not been freely given 
✨Bramacharya or non-lust: Merging with the One 
✨Aparigraha or non-possessiveness:  Non grasping  
 
Niyamas are how you treat yourself or your attitude towards yourself. 
✨Saucha - cleanliness 
✨Santosha - contentment  
✨Tapas - burning passion 
✨Svadhyaya - study of the sacred text and of one’s self 
✨Isvarapranidhans - Celebration of the Divine.  

These principles are the backbone of this practice. Take a listen to learn more!

{ESSENTIAL OILS FOR TRAVEL}⁠

I bet you’re wondering what you can and cannot travel with when jet-setting. If you’re planning to travel with doTERRA essential oils, here are some guidelines to keep in mind:

1.  Pack properly: To avoid spills, pack your essential oils in a separate ziplock bag or a sturdy carrying case.
2.  Label your oils: Label each bottle of essential oil with its name and intended use, especially if you’re carrying a blend or a customized recipe.
3.  Use protective packaging: To prevent glass bottles from breaking, wrap them in bubble wrap or store them in a padded case.
4.  Keep them cool: Essential oils can lose their potency when exposed to heat or sunlight, so store them in a cool and dark place, such as in your carry-on bag or hotel room.
5.  Be mindful of others: When using essential oils in public spaces, be considerate of others who may be sensitive to scents or have allergies.

By following these guidelines, you can travel with doTERRA essential oils safely and easily, and continue to enjoy their many benefits while on the go. 🌿✈️

Just the other day, I offered Breathwork and Sound Healing to 26 inmates at Donovan State Prison.  Apparently it was for their graduation from a 12 week course on emotional intelligence.  I get choked up thinking about it honestly.  I was so nervous the day of the event .. nothing was working right! I couldn’t get grounded for the life of me! 

But this is the humility of this life .. always in awe, always a student. I prayed for their souls days before; I prayed for my own well being, and I felt nervous and anxious all the way there. 

The moment I arrived … I felt a rush of love, of gratitude, and of curiosity.  I looked into the eyes of each attendee and my heart hurt.  I wanted to ask them how they got there. Keep those littles busy for hours with this Giant Scented Bubbles recipe.

⚈ 6 cups Cold Water
⚈ ½ cup Dish Soap
⚈ ½ cup Corn Starch
⚈ 1 TBSP Baking Powder
⚈ 1 TBSP Glycerin
⚈ 15 drops Citrus Bliss (or oil of choice)

Dissolve the cornstarch in cold water first. Add the remaining ingredients and stir slowly so as not to create a lot of froth. Allow to sit for a least one hour, stirring occasionally as the cornstarch settles. Some cornstarch may settle to the bottom, this will not affect the quality of your bubbles.

🫧 You will also need a giant bubble wand. 

🤩 Save this post for a reminder.

Most of you know me as Dana Damara, yoga teacher.  And while that is true, allow me to reintroduce myself: ⁠
⁠
Dana Damara – always evolving, always learning, always growing. ⁠
⁠
⁠I’m not just a yoga teacher … in fact, when people ask me what I “do’, I usually say, ⁠“I live and work in the field of energetics”. ⁠
⁠
Yes, I teach yoga, breathwork, sound healing and meditation, but I also offer Reiki and Healing sessions (in my new home office), house cleansing, crystal gridding of your home, marriage/baby blessings, wellness/leadership coaching, astrology readings, Shamanic journeys,  and  I am a DoTerra team leader.⁠
⁠
Over the years, I’ve picked up many modalities beyond “yoga teaching”. To be honest, yoga was the gateway for me, as it is for so many. ⁠
⁠
The mat was my safe place as it unraveled years of patterns, beliefs, and habits that I didn’t know existed.  It repeatedly made my body strong, continually cleared my mind, and allowed me to meet myself where I was at with compassion and grace. ⁠
⁠
This practice is so deep and vast that this lifetime will never be enough to integrate all the teachings, so I keep practicing and keep sharing; always a student even when I sit in the teacher’s seat. ⁠
⁠
I want to share with you that I am so much more than a yoga teacher, and it occurred to me that I have not shared all that I contribute.  It’s simply a timing thing, and a choice I’ve made to keep things simple. ⁠
⁠
I’ve learned a lot over the years, and if it’s one thing I know for sure, energy is at the base of it all. ⁠
⁠
Your internal energy creates everything … no exceptions.  And your home is a reflection of what you attract.  Don’t discount that cluttered closet, that “one drawer”, that box of photos, the closed drapes … it all matters. If you’re feeling off, and your home needs a little “lift” … reach out to me and we can talk about how to get you/your family back on track. ⁠
⁠
Transformative times, call for transformative practices. You are not just this body, remember that. ⁠

I taught my last class at this studio today. I decided to let it go because I feel like their vision and philosophy is too far out of alignment for me.

At the same time, I also believe that everyone needs to start somewhere. So stepping on your mat and doing what feels good for you… Is powerful!  There is no right or wrong in this practice… Only alignment for yourself.

I love the Yoga community. Everywhere I’ve lived and shared this practice, the Yoga community has become my family.

And I also believe that life is not a set sequence, not everyone can show up at the mat on time and need the same flow. The sound of OM for me personally, creates a sense of synergy and connection that just doesn’t happen when we skip it. 

Therefore, I will no longer be offering classes here on Sunday mornings. However, I am everywhere else… @alilamareabeachresort @yogaflowsf @thunderdomeranch … all in-service to this practice 

Thank you… For showing up and being the most authentic you there is… Can’t wait to see more of you somewhere on this path

Most of you know me as Dana Damara, yoga teacher.  And while that is true, allow me to reintroduce myself: ⁠
⁠
Dana Damara – always evolving, always learning, always growing. ⁠
⁠
⁠I’m not just a yoga teacher … in fact, when people ask me what I “do’, I usually say, ⁠“I live and work in the field of energetics”. ⁠
⁠
Yes, I teach yoga, breathwork, sound healing and meditation, but I also offer Reiki and Healing sessions (in my new home office), house cleansing, crystal gridding of your home, marriage/baby blessings, wellness/leadership coaching, astrology readings, Shamanic journeys,  and  I am a DoTerra team leader.⁠
⁠
Over the years, I’ve picked up many modalities beyond “yoga teaching”. To be honest, yoga was the gateway for me, as it is for so many. ⁠
⁠
The mat was my safe place as it unraveled years of patterns, beliefs, and habits that I didn’t know existed.  It repeatedly made my body strong, continually cleared my mind, and allowed me to meet myself where I was at with compassion and grace. ⁠
⁠
This practice is so deep and vast that this lifetime will never be enough to integrate all the teachings, so I keep practicing and keep sharing; always a student even when I sit in the teacher’s seat. ⁠
⁠
I want to share with you that I am so much more than a yoga teacher, and it occurred to me that I have not shared all that I contribute.  It’s simply a timing thing, and a choice I’ve made to keep things simple. ⁠
⁠
I’ve learned a lot over the years, and if it’s one thing I know for sure, energy is at the base of it all. ⁠
⁠
Your internal energy creates everything … no exceptions.  And your home is a reflection of what you attract.  Don’t discount that cluttered closet, that “one drawer”, that box of photos, the closed drapes … it all matters. If you’re feeling off, and your home needs a little “lift” … reach out to me and we can talk about how to get you/your family back on track. ⁠
⁠
Transformative times, call for transformative practices. You are not just this body, remember that. ⁠
⁠

My heart breaks and I'm mesmerized by the devastation on the island of Maui.  This event doesn't even begin to encapsulate the word trauma.  And while I have a ton of training and experience with trauma, I don't dare try and drop in and pretend I know how to support anyone in this situation right now.  

The only thing I do want to offer is this:  When things like this happen outside of our sphere, it's still happening to us in an indirect way.  We cannot turn a blind eye to anything.  However, we must lead with our hearts .. period.  So here's what I'm doing ...

	•	Praying ... and praying more
	•	Crying ... for the people left behind to sit in this tragedy
	•	Donating time and money to people in need @pacificbirthcollective 
	•	Finding gratitude for my life and the choices I have

I love @drsarahannerothman with my whole heart and her and I are going to deliver an INCREDIBLE retreat in Todos Santos @topiaretreat … how do I know? 

Because when her and I work together magic happens ... period.  

But she's in the thick of this devastation. She lives on this island and I'm sure has been impacted directly in some way, shape or form.  I asked her who to donate to 

She said: Pacific Birth Collective:  They provide Education, Support, and Advocacy for Birth and Wellness Choices Across Hawai'i. They are doing some amazing work over there and if you are looking for a way to help the people of Maui DIRECTLY ... donate to these women. 

Living here on the mainland, we can keep this tragedy at bay ... but she is in it.  Therefore my plea is to take a second and do one of the things listed above and drop into your life and remember you only get one.

THANK YOU everyone who reached out yesterday on my birthday. I really appreciate the love.  Here are a few things that were on my mind yesterday: 

This is a good life 
Your decisions DO shape your future 
Love the past as much as you wish for the future 
And then remember to be present only 
I am loved. 

My heart is full and grieving all at the same time. This chapter I’ve been in for the last 21 years is over and it’s like, shit, where did those years go?  The time spent raising two girls, building a career, the lines on my face … all beautiful and yet … wow, that was fleeting. 

As I look back at the past, observe my egoic need to “know” the future, and then subsequently feel into what needs to go, get curious about what is showing up in small lights of hope and connection I am curious, peaceful, hopeful, sad, happy, proud, confused, a little regretful but most of all grateful. 

Thank you for being in my life.  Cheers to the next chapter.

After a lot of thought, I have decided not to teach classes at Compass Rose. I know this may be disappointing however, I have given it a lot of thought.  And instead of glossing over it, bypassing my reasons, I am giving it a voice.  
 
My issue is not with the space, but instead, with the way I was treated and spoken to by the person in charge of the space rental. I will not name names, or even go into the story around the events leading up to my decision.  I kept that for my email to the people who gave this person the power. Power is an interesting thing … we can use it to help, belittle, or harm others.  
 
I’ll save that for another post.  
 
My experience with this person was one of disrespect, degradation, and just plain old impoliteness.  My biggest deliberation in accepting this treatment, and offering the classes anyway was honestly, the commitment I made to the community by offering this class.  
 
However, and here’s the biggest, most important piece that I really want you to hear:  
 
✨I am no longer willing to jeopardize my integrity just to make other people happy.  🌟

While making my decision today, I had similar conversations with clients, colleagues and friends all experiencing similar situations.  

Thank you, Venus in your shadow ... clearing out those little “whispies” Thank you Mercury Cazimi for keeping it real.  
 
If this speaks to you, use the mantra. If you were wanting to come to those time slots, don’t worry … it’s coming.  But not at the cost of my personal integrity.  Many rounds of Om.  🕉️
 
Love you
D xo

Yoga allowed me to dissolve the old stories in my body… but alas, it was only one layer.  Every time I practiced I shed a layer of grief, shame, guilt, doubt … 

Yoga opened my heart, made my body strong, and has kept me healthier as I get wiser in my life.  All the tools I gathered along the way supported me in this most recent chapter of my life in raising two girls on my own. 

Sound healing relaxed my brain and calmed my nervous system, allowing me to learn to actually receive and not push to do it all alone.  Essential oils don’t just make my home smell good, but heal my body from the inside out. 

But the breathwork … my Goddess, the breathwork.  It’s like nothing else.

It brought me to places that my mind kept me from going.  To the places I feared going as I was fearful of “losing control.” As a single mother, I HAD TO keep it together. There wasn’t time for a mushroom trip in the forest, a 10 day Vipassana, or even a weekend of sexual romping with a lover.  There was always something “to do”. And unless you have been in this position please … do not comment about how “allowing things to flow” would have made it easier … that’s not what this post is about.

Truth be told, I wish I had found breathwork while I was running that single mom chapter.  It’s an hour long session and you go deeper than you can imagine. You get “behind” the thoughts that ruminate and find the answers you seek.  I like to take 45 minutes of breath, 10 of sound, and then 15 of journaling.  It’s opened pathways to my heart and cracked it wide open. It allowed the rage inside to finally be released and freed my body from all the pain I’ve held in all these years. 

I know what pain not expressed does to the body and I’m so grateful for this practice. You should come and try it sometime.  You’ll never believe the power you have inside until you witness it for yourself. 

Tues/Thurs EVERY WEEK at 7am

I know, I know. It might not always be something that we are thinking about, but our makeup brushes are probably in the need of some cleaning. Give this a try! ⁠
⁠
All you need are 3 ingredients.⁠
⁠
✅ 2 Tablespoons of Fractionated Coconut Oil (FCO)⁠
✅ 5 drops Melaleuca Oil⁠
✅ 5 drops Grapefruit Oil⁠
⁠
Instructions:⁠
Add fractionated coconut oil and essential oils to a small bowl⁠
Swirl brushes in the bowl for 30 seconds or until you see the makeup start to come out⁠
Rub in a circular motion on the palm of your hand to help get the makeup out⁠
Rinse brush under warm water, gently squeezing bristles until the water runs clear⁠
Let brushes dry for 4 hours or until dry. Repeat once a month or as needed.⁠
⁠
How often do you clean your makeup brushes?⁠

On September 29th, 2023 we have the last 🌕Super Full Moon 🌕 before Eclipse Season begins.  

The Moon is at 6° Aries and doesn’t make aspects with any other planets.  However, the Moon is sharing space with Chiron and the North Node:  healing our karma.

This Full Moon brings us back to March 2023, when we had the Aries New Moon, followed by powerful Eclipses.  The intentions you set, way back then are most likely up for completion, clarity, or release.  

This Full Moon wants you to be consciously aware, so you can purge what is no longer attuned to the higher vibration of who you are.  This energy wants you to be so attuned that you can’t help but follow your instincts and tune everything else out.
 
Mars is a bit active with this Full Moon:  Opposing Chiron and sextile to Venus.  Mars wants action toward healing. Accountability, courage, self-confidence, and prepared action.  With the sextile to Venus, the Divine Feminine and Sacred Masculine are conspiring for harmony and connection.   
 
Mercury opposite Neptune brings awareness around your thoughts. Specifically aiming to distinguish between reality and illusion.  Things will become clearer and clearer, as if the fog lifts.  Stay awake. Use your imagination, develop your day-to-day from there. But know when the illusion is carrying you away. 
 
Here’s a few takeaways: 
 
🌟This is not a good time to make firm decisions. 
🌟It’s a time to gather information .. at least until a few days after the Full Moon.
🌟Take care of your heart.
🌟Stay out of the mind.
🌟Put your crystals out! You won’t be doing that on the Lunar Eclipse!

I’ve been deeply inspired by this practice we call Breathwork.  So inspired that I’ve put an email campaign out there now through the end of October.  

I continually dig deeper in my life, it’s just who I am.  And I share what I know to be true for me so that in some way, shape, or form … it may support you.   Breathwork has become so valuable to me that I’ve put musings onto my site, onto my Blog Page, that is reserved for really important topics like this one.  
 
This is an excerpt, however, if you’re curious you’ll subscribe to my newsletter and receive all the updates OR you’ll go to my Blog page and read the article in its entirety 
 
The journey starts on the mat, relieving the tension in the bones, muscles, and joints. Strengthening our vessel for this life. We practice alignment, and asana as if it were the be all and do all. From there we are awakened and can never go back to sleep.  So, we dive into the Deep End of our life, where infinite possibilities exist. 
 
You have this vessel you call your body, but you are an infinite being that is on borrowed time in this body, and on this Earth. You have a myriad of lessons you said, as a soul, that you wanted to learn, in this lifetime, as we know it to be, our Earth School.
 
I’ve captured glimpses of what this philosophy really means, but I didn’t understand it until I did a psychedelic journey with my therapist.
 
Maybe you’re not quite ready for that - so try breathwork.  
It’s the bridge between the deep end, and the shallow end. With breathwork, you are truly still in the “driver’s seat” of the practice. You call the shots.  You can go as deep as you’d like and take the morsels in the bite-size you can handle.  
 
I consider myself a gate keeper of this work.  And I am here to support you.  Please, read more, subscribe, or reach out to me if you’d like more.
 
I’m taking clients now through November 15th.  2023 and would love to support you on a new path of truth, freedom and love.

Saturday, October 14, 2023 at 10:55am pst, brings us a October New Moon Solar Eclipse at 21° Libra.

New Moons are generally a fantastic time to start something new, cultivate a new project, shift your focus, or let go of old habits.  When the New Moon is eclipsed, it makes that energy even more potent.  Everything feels bigger, brighter, more intense, and potentially triggering.  

Because the New Moon is in Libra, the theme for this energy is balance, relationships, intimacy, and duality.   Since the New Moon is conjunct the South Node, we are collectively and individually letting go of the past …. Again.  

Thank Goddess we shed continually in this life:  always evolving and expanding our awareness, perception and ability to see deeper and deeper truth.  
 
Eclipses happen in “bundles”,  so they travel in pairs of Solar and Lunar; and usually happen twice a year. The previous eclipse of this year happened in April 2023 … think back to what was happening then … 
 
🌟What have you learned?
🌟How have you grown?
🌟What are you willing to take responsibility for?  
 
Mars opposite Saturn will hold the line of your responsibility and karmic duty.  Igniting you into action, calling in courage and confidence.  
New Moon opposite Chiron and conjunct will support you with clarity around any and all healing opportunities.  

How should you best use this New Moon energy?  

💕Rest … a lot
💕Take time outs … a lot 
💕Act on what feels right … follow your intuition 
💕Refrain from making any important decisions 
💕Follow your creative impulses 
💕Re-evaluate your circle of friends 
💕Say yes to emotions, no to draining activities

🌟1:1 BREATHWORK SESSIONS✨ You have a choice ... you really, really do. ⁠
⁠
We’re in the midst of a paradigm shift … are you aware?  The entire way we do things in this life has been shifting, both collectively and individually. � �And we unfortunately keep gripping to the old ways, continue trying to change other people, or distract ourselves by being too busy to notice. �⁠
⁠
We’re in a real pressure cooker right now. ⁠
⁠
Too busy to do anything outside of our comfort zone, asleep at the wheel of our lives, concerned about the future, ruminating over the past. And during all this, we have had glimpses of that awakening we all talk about, haven’t we? The glimpses keep us going …  but for how long? We step in but it’s REALLY hard, isn’t it?  There’s no path … no sure-fire way to shift. �⁠
⁠
So we go back to sleep. ⁠
⁠
 �Here’s the truth, if you want to shift your life, you can.  You have the choice … you’ve just forgotten.  But the Universe hasn’t forgotten, so you’ll get real uncomfortable at some point, and then you’ll remember. ⁠
⁠
If you’ve survived tumultuous times, you know what I mean.�⁠
* This is YOUR life.⁠
* You are in charge.⁠
* You have agency and choice. ⁠
⁠
The only thing you can control is your emotional reaction to your life … once you master that, you’ve mastered the navigational set point of your life.  But that point is very misguided via ancestral beliefs, societal expectations, and outdated perceptions of ourselves and our role in this life. � �Want to know a few tidbits of info that have helped me? ⁠
⁠
1. Stay true to yourself. ⁠
2. Check in with your body. ⁠
3. Speak up without apologizing.⁠
4. Stop making excuses.⁠
5. REST.⁠
⁠

Showing up as your best Self can be challenging.  We are riddled with patterns, societal constructs, self-doubt, and old childhood trauma. ⁠

⁠
Did you know that your energy proceeds you (the physical you) by about a mile?  Meaning when you walk into a room, everyone in that room can feel you. ⁠
⁠
We are in constant motion, being directed by subconscious patterns, and outside influence.  And since we are magnetic beings, we pick up on everyone else as well. ⁠
⁠
Sounds exhausting, doesn’t it? ⁠
⁠
I mean how do you know if you are living YOUR life, or someone else’s? Here are a few questions I have for you: ⁠

Are you living by those core values? ⁠
Are you telling the truth to the people in your life?⁠

Are you in integrity with your highest Self?⁠
What do you stand for?⁠

These are questions I ask MYSELF on the daily.  I’m here to support you coming home to yourself, showing up authentically, feeling inspired and alive, and communicating your truth eloquently without fear, guilt, or shame.⁠

I remember this day like it was yesterday. 

I was fairly new to SF and was doing a photoshoot with my friend @elipoint.  

The girls were 9 and 12 and I was just getting my bearings.  I was so scared honestly: new city, new people, new home.  I felt like the small fish in the big ocean, and everything was overwhelming.  
 
I knew my practice would carry us all.  Not always easy to sit on that cushion or roll out my mat, but I did it.  Every day.  Never perfect but I still did it.  I’m writing again, putting together my book finally, and it’s bringing up so much. 

Thank you @ommagazine for publishing an oldie but a goodie. This one is from Oms from Heart, my second book. I love this one.  Take a read at 🌟THE LINK IN MY BIO 🌟but here is an excerpt: 
 
“The other day, I’m in the car with my youngest daughter and she asked me, “Mom, is there an end to the sky?” And I said, “Um no honey. It’s infinite.” And she said, “Infinite... like energy?” And I said, “Yup, just like that.” 

She sat there for quite a while looking up and out of the sunroof. As if she was trying to figure it all out.

We didn’t talk that much after that, but I could tell the wheels were turning. 

It got me thinking about the word foundation and how daunting it can be. 

I mean, if the Earth is spinning and the sky is infinite, are we really standing on any type of foundation?

Yes, most certainly we are. Ourselves.

I contemplated foundation for a while before I wrote this. And I remembered a few times in my life when I had no physical foundation.”

🌟1:1 BREATHWORK SESSIONS✨ You have a choice ... you really, really do. ⁠
⁠
We’re in the midst of a paradigm shift … are you aware? 

The entire way we do things in this life has been shifting, both collectively and individually. And we unfortunately keep gripping to the old ways, continue trying to change other people, or distract ourselves by being too busy to notice. 
⁠
We’re in a real pressure cooker right now. ⁠
⁠
Too busy to do anything outside of our comfort zone, asleep at the wheel of our lives, concerned about the future, ruminating over the past. 

And during all this, we have had glimpses of that awakening we all talk about, haven’t we? The glimpses keep us going …  but for how long? We step in but it’s REALLY hard, isn’t it? 

There’s no path … no sure-fire way to shift. 

So we go back to sleep. ⁠
⁠
 Here’s the truth, if you want to shift your life, you can.  You have the choice … you’ve just forgotten. 

But the Universe hasn’t forgotten, so you’ll get real uncomfortable at some point, and then you’ll remember. ⁠
⁠
If you’ve survived tumultuous times, you know what I mean.
* This is YOUR life.⁠
* You are in charge.⁠
* You have agency and choice. ⁠
⁠
The only thing you can control is your emotional reaction to your life … once you master that, you’ve mastered the navigational set point of your life.  But that point is very misguided via ancestral beliefs, societal expectations, and outdated perceptions of ourselves and our role in this life. Want to know a few tidbits of info that have helped me? ⁠
⁠
1. Stay true to yourself. ⁠
2. Check in with your body. ⁠
3. Speak up without apologizing.⁠
4. Stop making excuses.⁠
5. REST.⁠
⁠

In May of 2023, I tore my meniscus.  It was such a bummer because well honestly, I had just healed my neck from 2022, AND I could feel my body heading into full blown menopause. 

What a shit show.  So what did I do? I chose to ignore the injury … after all, it came at a horrible time. I was heading to Italy and Greece for a month soon, and I didn’t have “time” to stop and pause.  So a few days prior to me leaving for my revered trip, I hurt my knee even more, to the point that I couldn’t even walk. 

Did that stop me? Nope. I kept going and led two pretty successful retreats in Europe, even though my luggage never made it.  Anyway … this post is not about that story, which I’m sure we can all interpret.  This post is about a come back. 

Since May, I had not been able to practice, run, get my heart rate up like I like, or do all the things I love doing.  I gained about 10 pounds, something I haven’t experienced since childbirth.  And my mental and emotional health was at an all time low.  I literally skipped my most recent birthday - very unlike this Leo. 

We all feel times like this eh?  But thankfully I have tools and a community. 

I’ve dropped back into using my @puriumhp thanks to my neighbor’s inspiration. 
I started practicing again when I came to visit @reddragonyoga and @yogaflowsf. And I’ve been finally getting my heart rate up at @thebxngclub and using all the weights.  It’s amazing … our body isn’t it? 

Don’t ever let anyone tell you that because of your injury, your age, or your resources, that you can’t do something. You can .. it’s a choice.  You have to want it bad enough and be disciplined enough to make choices to “get there”. 

And at the same time, honor those moments where it’s obvious that your body wants you to slow the f*&K down and listen.  There are big shifts happening in my life and I want to be healthy, happy, and sexy as all get out.  Not for you, not for my European man, but for me.   Cheers to this next chapter

Prayer in motion 
Sacred movement 
Moving from the heart ❤️ 

Thank you for tonight @yogaflowsf 
 I ❤️ you

🍫Snacking chocolates infused with dōTERRA essential oils make a quick and easy item to bring to any event, give as a gift or even keep for yourself!⁠
⁠
What you need: 1 cup dark chocolate chips, 1 tsp coconut oil, ½ cup almonds, Peppermint and/or Wild Orange essential oil.⁠
⁠
Place chocolate chips and coconut oil in a double boiler or you can put a glass bowl on top of a gentle boiling pot of water and melt until smooth. Add in essential oil of choice (note: 1-2 drops is perfect for a subtle taste, add more as needed!) ⁠
⁠
Pour melted chocolate onto wax paper on a cookie sheet and spread the chocolate around with a spoon. Crush almonds (or candy canes!) and sprinkle over the chocolate layer. Place in the refrigerator and allow to chill. Once solidified, break into pieces and enjoy!⁠
⁠
Which are you making: Peppermint with candy cane or Wild Orange with almonds?⁠

✨Sagittarius New Moon:  12.12.2023 at 3:33pm pst.  ✨
 
So much power, so much potential, and yet, with Mercury retrograde, so much patient must be present as well. Sag is ruled by Jupiter, so expansion is the name of the game.  Faith, higher knowledge, wisdom, good fortune, luck and justice.  
 
12.12 is also powerful in numerology as it represents all that is moving into a higher state of consciousness.  12 signs of the zodiac wheel, 12 houses, 12 inches in a foot, 12 months in the calendar year.  This energy represents endings so new beginnings can take place. 
 
If we can ALWAYS come back to the remembrance: we are living in this body to learn, grow, and evolve …. Life gets fun!  We enrolled in this Earth School so remember that … and this New Moon is a culmination of all that we have learned over the last 13 lunations.  
 
This New Moon holds fiery, passionate energy thanks to Mars still holding close to the Sun. Be mindful to respond and not react. Mars can act as a beautiful boost to help us spring into action quicker with more potency behind us.  Use this energy wisely.  
 
Mercury goes into retrograde in this energy of the New Moon so we have a “pull-back” energy as well.  Refrain, revisit, review, reignite, all those “re” words come into play.  So the best advice for this New Moon is to get into balance with what you desire, and what your heart wants before you go stomping into the New Year.  Mercury stays in retrograde until 1.1.2024…now isn’t that useful? Move slowly and get organized.  Double check plans and be extra patient with yourself and others! 
 
One more thing to note: Neptune goes direct just before this New Moon so those dreams will begin manifesting.  Distinguish between what is real and what is an illusion … it’s time to Dream Big lovelies.  Bliss is not a destination, it’s a choice.  Choose wisely.

I love this city.  Everything about it. 

It’s a vibe. 
It’s a buzz. 
It’s a huge part of my life. 
I hustle here. 
I belong here. 
I am challenged here. 

Not a huge fan of living on top of each other, spacial proximity isn’t aligned with my needs, but the vibe makes up for it. 

I love walking up the stairs to teach at YogaFlow and at the Castro. 
I love coming into a yoga room where everyone knows your name. 
I love offering a practice to and practicing alongside a community that is so receptive and open that’s almost like …. well, 

we all just belong together. 

I’ve been fortunate enough to teach and play here for years. And because of @yogaflowsf, I was able to keep my tether to the SF Community since I moved away in 2018. 

It’s like a boyfriend I can’t quite break up with.  Nor do I have any plans to do so. 

SF you’re my happy pill in just the right dosage.   Because the life I created in Cardiff is also a salve. 

It soothes my soul. 
It rests my heart. 
It grounds me in and makes me feel so small against that ocean. 
I love my garden, and my yard, and my neighbors who have become family. 
I love my fruit trees, and my roses, and my fountains. 
I can walk everywhere if I want and every restaurant is like home. 

This community has become my home too.  I feel at home here too. 

So what to do … 

Nothing. Enjoy the grace of the present moment and anchor deeply in the ride of the wave. Trying to anchor into “one or the other” is silly — life is in constant motion and right now, in this moment, I am lucky enough to get to experience both and all. 

Thank you SF … I’ll see you soon. (NYE and NYD and BOC!) 

Thank you Cardiff, you calm my restless heart.

Another day, another DIY! 😆 Today we are going to talk about making our own essential oil candles!⁠
⁠
What you will need: 4 cups beeswax pellets, 1 cup of coconut oil, cotton wicks, 4 oz mason jars, and your favorite essential oils.⁠
⁠
Melt the beeswax and coconut oil in the microwave. While still a liquid, add your essential oils (I suggest 20 drops Holiday Joy, 20 drops Holiday Peace or 20 drops Northern Escape). Add a drop of wax to the center of the mason jar and position the wick. Carefully pour the wax mixture into the mason jars and allow the candles to set and cool. Cut the wick to about ½ inch about the wax. This will make 4 candles.⁠
⁠
How many of these are you going to make? This is a great way to ditch those toxic candles once and for all!⁠

We have probably heard of aromatherapy playdough by now, but have you ever thought of Aromatherapy with Water Beads?! ⁠
⁠
Water beads are an amazing sensory activity for kids or adults alike. All you will need are water beads, essential oils of your choice, a bucket with scoops to play and water.⁠
⁠
Mix together your oil of choice with your water (try 1 drop of essential oil per 1 cup of water). Pour water beads into a bucket and add the water/essential oil mixture. It will take a few minutes for the beads to expand. All set to play! Scoop the beads, run them through your fingers… just relax!⁠
⁠
What essential oil would you use here? I am thinking Balance all the way!⁠
⁠

Recently I’ve posted about classes, workshops, trainings, retreats, my books, products I love and create, and trips in and out of SF.  
 
Feels like a good time to reintroduce myself as new folks are here, and things are shifting.  Graduated from University of Phoenix 1996, took off for two years and traveled abroad on boats as a chef.  Came home to SD and stepped into the yoga world.    Moved to WA and dove deep, opening my own yoga studio and launching my first 200-hour YTT.  Launched the first ever prenatal yoga program at the hospitals in SW Washington.  Moved to SF and swam with the big fish in the yoga world; learned a lot, loved it, and still can’t break up with that city; nor do I want to. 
 
Launched the first yoga for teens program in the schools of SF and Marin offering social and emotional learning, along with yoga and meditation.  
 
Moved home to San Diego, stayed on the yoga train, incorporating astrology, doTERRA, sound healing, Reiki, breathwork, women’s circles, Moon  ceremonies, and wellness coaching to my bag of tricks.    Created the Moon Phase Journal, the DailyIAMDeck, SoulMedicine podcast, and grew my doTERRA team.  During the pandemic, I created DanaDamaraYoga, an online portal with over 400 classes and tutorials, uploaded 12 advanced teacher trainings courses into DanaDamaraEvolution, and launched Embodied Feminine Wisdom, an online women’s group that thrived during lockdown.  
 
I’ve been hosting yoga retreats all along the West Coast and internationally for over two decades now, and find a new place to bring adventurous souls every year!  
 Now I’m aiming for bi-city lifestyle.  Cardiff soothes my soul, the ocean is a necessity for me.  But Sausalito expands my vision, and the city ignites my heart.  So ... here I am, in the 1D world, re-introducing myself to you, bowing in gratitude for this life and all the amazing souls I get to connect with every single day.  
 
If you have crossed my path, thank you.   Your words, your presence, and your love have touched me in some way; enough to offer up gratitude, grace and love … thank you.

{WEEK 6} Journey through the Chakras: Ajna:  The Third Eye Chakra. 

The sixth chakra is the gateway to enlightenment – to wisdom and insight into our inner world.  It is the home of intuition, dreams and visions.  The sixth chakra is often called the third eye – the seat of consciousness that lies directly behind and between the two eyes.  It is here where we dive into the subtler realms of energy and spirit.  This is where we perceive truth and reality – letting go of illusion and denial.
Any imbalance in this chakra shows up in the eyes, head, and pineal gland. 

Our chakras get misaligned all the time – every day! It’s our job to bring them into balance and it’s not that hard if it’s attended to on a regular basis.  We can be excessive in a chakra, or deficient and something as simple as breathing or moving our bodies can help us rebalance.  
 
If you are a member of our portal, you can watch this clip and practice on your own.  It’s a Surya Namaskar specifically for the root chakra so you can do this in 8 minutes a day … at home!  Join for as little a $45 a month and try all that we have to offer.

{KICKSTART YOUR HEALTHY HABITS}⁠
⁠
A warm, luxurious bath is sometimes just what you need at the end of a long or stressful day. You can take your relaxation to the next level by combining essential oils and bath salts.⁠
As the epsom salt and oils interact with the warm water, you will get to enjoy the lovely aroma of essential oils as they soothe the body and enliven the senses—making your soak in the tub even more rejuvenating. ⁠
Ingredients⁠
1 cup Epsom salt⁠
10 drops Lavender oil⁠
Instructions⁠
Add Lavender oil to Epsom salt and stir together.⁠
Draw a warm bath and add ¼–½ cup of Epsom salt to the tub.⁠
⁠
⁠
Are you “team bath” or “team shower”? ⁠

One of the most anticipated transits of the decade is happening Sunday … 
 
Pluto moves from Capricorn to Aquarius.
Why is this such a big deal?  Because this “dwarf planet” is about death, rebirth, inner transformation, empowerment, power struggles and wants nothing more than for us to align with our soul’s truth.  
Pluto has been in the Earth sign of Capricorn since 2008 and he’s been focused on slowly dismantling structures and hierarchies since then so we can truly see that Power to the People and Humanity as a whole is really where the heart must reside if we want to survive.  

On January 21, 2024, Pluto moves into Aquarius, just after the Sun moves into Aquarius so there’s a little extra power punch of transformation happening there.
In September of 2024, Pluto dips out and for a couple of months, but then in November, Pluto will remain in Aquarius until 2044.   

When Pluto changes signs our lives as a collective, will change in unprecedented ways, it’s inevitable.  

If you can go back first, to 2008 and just remember where you were. Then think about the lessons that you’ve sat with since then.  What power struggles have you been dealing with?  And then, go back to January 12, 2020 when we had that powerful stellium in Capricorn just before the world shut down.  What has happened for you since then with regards to your empowerment?  Where have you been challenged?  What’s an underlying theme for you?  

Know that all of that is now over.  Pluto wants you to get rid of what has decayed or turned rotten, and allow it to be compost for your life.  

Listen to the full recording on my Youtube Channel and set yourself up for an abundant, expansive, incredible new era. 
Yes, this is a brand new era we are entering and the old will get heavy really quickly if you don’t let it go.
